            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and reduce the heat to low, then add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and stir through your <strong>mango chutney </strong>and cook for 5-7 min or until the sauce has thickened to a curry-like consistency</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, cover with a lid and set aside for later – this is your <strong>katsu sauce</strong></p><p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan with 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
